quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  20,118,"Verily, you have (a promise from Us) that you will never be hungry therein nor naked."
  20,119,"And you (will) suffer not from thirst therein nor from the sun’s heat."
  20,120,"Then Shaitân (Satan) whispered to him, saying: "
  21,94,"So whoever does righteous good deeds while he is a believer (in the Oneness of Allâh - Islâmic Monotheism), his efforts will not be rejected. Verily We record it for him (in his Book of deeds).{1}",footnotes:1:[{21:94} See the footnote of (Verse 9:121).]
  21,95,"And a ban is laid on every town (population) which We have destroyed that they shall not return (to this world again, nor repent to Us)."
  21,96,"Until, when Ya’jûj and Ma’jûj (Gog and Magog){1} are let loose (from their barrier), and they swoop down from every mound.",footnotes:1:[{21:96} See the footnote of (Verse 18:94).]
  22,70,"Know you not that Allâh knows all that is in the heaven and on the earth? Verily, it is (all) in the Book (Al-Lauh-al-Mahfûz). Verily that is easy for Allâh."
  22,71,"And they worship besides Allâh others for which He has sent down no authority, and of which they have no knowledge; and for the Zâlimûn (wrong-doers, polytheists and disbelievers in the Oneness of Allâh) there is no helper."
  22,72,"And when Our Clear Verses are recited to them, you will notice a denial on the faces of the disbelievers! They are nearly ready to attack with violence those who recite Our Verses to them. Say: "
  23,46,"To Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) and his chiefs, but they behaved insolently and they were people self-exalting (by disobeying their Lord, and exalting themselves over and above the Messenger of Allâh)."
  23,47,"They said: "
  23,48,"So they denied them both [Mûsâ (Moses) and Hârûn (Aaron)] and became of those who were destroyed."
  24,28,"And if you find no one therein, still, enter not until permission has been given. And if you are asked to go back, go back, for it is purer for you. And Allâh is All-Knower of what you do."
  24,29,"There is no sin on you that you enter (without taking permission) houses uninhabited (i.e. not possessed by anybody), (when) you have any interest in them. And Allâh has knowledge of what you reveal and what you conceal."
  24,30,"Tell the believing men to lower their gaze (from looking at forbidden things), and protect their private parts (from illegal sexual acts). That is purer for them. Verily, Allâh is All-Aware of what they do."